  "texts": [
    "An illustration is shown in fig. 20, where the red curve denotes the ground truth, the blue curve is the predicted mean at the final time step, and the shaded region indicates the empirical confidence interval defined by ±3 standard deviations.",
    "To evaluate uncertainty quality, we report two standard metrics:",
    "• CRPS (Continuous Ranked Probability Score) measures the accuracy and sharpness of probabilistic forecasts by comparing the predicted distribution to the true outcome.",
    "Lower CRPS indicates better probabilistic calibration.",
    "• RMSCE (Root Mean Squared Calibration Error) quantifies calibration by comparing predicted confidence intervals with empirical coverage."
  ],
